## 👥 Roles & Permissions

| Feature               | Admin | Doctor | Receptionist |
|-----------------------|:-----:|:------:|:------------:|
| Manage Users          | ✅    | ❌     | ❌           |
| Manage Employees      | ✅    | ❌     | ❌           |
| Manage Departments    | ✅    | ❌     | ❌           |
| Create/Edit Patients  | ✅    | ❌     | ✅           |
| View Patients         | ✅    | ✅     | ✅           |
| Medical Records       | ✅    | ✅     | ❌           |
| Create Appointments   | ✅    | ❌     | ✅           |
| View Appointments     | ✅    | ✅ (own)| ✅ (all)    |
| Create Meetings       | ✅    | ❌     | ❌           |
| View Meetings         | ✅    | ✅     | ❌           |
| Notifications         | ❌    | ✅     | ✅           |
| Edit Profile          | ✅    | ✅     | ✅           |

---

## 🔔 Notification System

Notifications are triggered automatically:

| Event                        | Notified        |
|------------------------------|-----------------|
| Appointment created          | Doctor assigned |
| Appointment date/time changed| Doctor assigned |
| Appointment cancelled        | Doctor + Receptionists |
| Appointment deleted          | Doctor + Receptionists |

Notifications are polled every **30 seconds** and displayed with an unread badge in the navbar.

---

## ⚙️ Installation & Setup

### Prerequisites
- Node.js v18+
- MongoDB (local or Atlas)

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/apollonia-dental.git
cd apollonia-dental
```

### 2. Backend setup
```bash
cd backend
npm install
```

Create a `.env` file in `backend/`:
```env
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/apollonia
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_key_here
```

### 3. Frontend setup
```bash
cd ../frontend
npm install
```

### 4. Seed the database
```bash
cd ../backend
node seed/seed.js
```

### 5. Run the application

**Terminal 1 — Backend:**
```bash
cd backend
npm run dev
```

**Terminal 2 — Frontend:**
```bash
cd frontend
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:5173](http://localhost:5173)

